            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">5</p>
            <p>accompany me. We went—<persName>Dr. Henry</persName><lb/> I said will you answer me a
                few<lb/> questions? I want to be answered<lb/> exactly<add>?</add>, as on <hi
                    rend="underline">your</hi> answers depend my<lb/> marriage with <persName>Mr.
                    P.</persName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">If I marry <persName>Mr. P.</persName> can any one point<lb/> their
                finger at us in scorn and say<lb/> they have done wrongly? “In Madam.”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">If we marry and have children<lb/> are they legitimate? “Yes
                Madam”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Will any reproach be attached to<lb/> those children through our
                marriage?<lb/> “No Madam”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Well, what do you want Doctor?<lb/> I'll tell you what you <hi
                    rend="underline">can</hi> do, you<lb/> can go to <placeName>Germany</placeName>
                and get “Kalitza”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I indignantly answered “I will<lb/> see them further first” I was
                    <hi rend="underline">so</hi><lb/> very angry.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Dr. Henry</persName>
                <hi rend="underline">then</hi> said “Now I <del>will</del><lb/> am going to take off
                my gown (<add>?</add><lb/> the action to the words) and told you</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">6</p>
            <p><hi rend="underline">confidentially</hi> that had you <hi rend="underline">had</hi>
                Kalitza<lb/> you then dared not marry him.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I rose joyfully “Thank you Doctor<lb/> (said I) those news was an
                act of parliament<lb/> but what a coach and six<add>?</add> could drive<lb/>
                through. <persName>Mr. P.</persName> we will be married.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Dr. Henry</persName> said any Jewish mi-<lb/>-nister could
                marry us, and we then<lb/> applied to the <persName>Revd. Dr. Eckman</persName>
                who<lb/> married us.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="underline">If</hi> I have sinned, which I hope<lb/> I have
                not, it lays at <persName>Dr. Henry's</persName> door,<lb/> for as I hope to meet my
                maker hereafter<lb/> I had resolved had he said <hi rend="underline">no</hi> I would<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">not</hi> have married.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The doctors' refusal arose, not as<lb/>
                <persName>Theophilus</persName> states from <persName>Dr. Henry's</persName><lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">conviction</hi> of wrong <hi rend="underline">but</hi> because
                of<lb/> in cabal suscitated<add>?</add> by <persName>A. B. Ephraim</persName><lb/>
                and others against him to catch<lb/> him tripping</p>
            <p>***</p>
            <p>P. S. I should feel regret at mentioning</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">7</p>
            <p><persName>Dr. Henry's</persName> confidential remarks to me,<lb/> were it not that
                being so well acquainted<lb/> with the Doctor's Phraseology, I feel but<lb/> little
                scruple in asserting that “<persName>Theophilus</persName>”<lb/> and the Doctor do
                not live <hi rend="underline">very</hi> far<lb/> apart.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">***</p>
        </body>
